4446 ASTFileSignature ASTWriter::WriteAST(Sema &SemaRef,
4447  const std::string &OutputFile,
4448  Module *WritingModule, StringRef isysroot,
4449  bool hasErrors,
4450  bool ShouldCacheASTInMemory) {
4451  WritingAST = true;
4452 
4453  ASTHasCompilerErrors = hasErrors;
4454 
4455  // Emit the file header.
4456  Stream.Emit((unsigned)'C', 8);
4457  Stream.Emit((unsigned)'P', 8);
4458  Stream.Emit((unsigned)'C', 8);
4459  Stream.Emit((unsigned)'H', 8);
4460 
4461  WriteBlockInfoBlock();
4462 
4463  Context = &SemaRef.Context;
4464  PP = &SemaRef.PP;
4465  this->WritingModule = WritingModule;
4466  ASTFileSignature Signature =
4467  WriteASTCore(SemaRef, isysroot, OutputFile, WritingModule);
4468  Context = nullptr;
4469  PP = nullptr;
4470  this->WritingModule = nullptr;
4471  this->BaseDirectory.clear();
4472 
4473  WritingAST = false;
4474  if (ShouldCacheASTInMemory) {
4475  // Construct MemoryBuffer and update buffer manager.
4476  ModuleCache.addBuiltPCM(OutputFile,
4477  llvm::MemoryBuffer::getMemBufferCopy(
4478  StringRef(Buffer.begin(), Buffer.size())));
4479  }
4480  return Signature;
4481 }
4482 
4483 template<typename Vector>
4484 static void AddLazyVectorDecls(ASTWriter &Writer, Vector &Vec,
4485  ASTWriter::RecordData &Record) {
4486  for (typename Vector::iterator I = Vec.begin(nullptr, true), E = Vec.end();
4487  I != E; ++I) {
4488  Writer.AddDeclRef(*I, Record);
4489  }
4490 }
4491 
4492 ASTFileSignature ASTWriter::WriteASTCore(Sema &SemaRef, StringRef isysroot,
4493  const std::string &OutputFile,
4494  Module *WritingModule) {
4495  using namespace llvm;
4496 
4497  bool isModule = WritingModule != nullptr;
4498 
4499  // Make sure that the AST reader knows to finalize itself.
4500  if (Chain)
4501  Chain->finalizeForWriting();
4502 
4503  ASTContext &Context = SemaRef.Context;
4504  Preprocessor &PP = SemaRef.PP;
4505 
4506  // Set up predefined declaration IDs.
4507  auto RegisterPredefDecl = [&] (Decl *D, PredefinedDeclIDs ID) {
4508  if (D) {
4509  assert(D->isCanonicalDecl() && "predefined decl is not canonical");
4510  DeclIDs[D] = ID;
4511  }
4512  };
4513  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.getTranslationUnitDecl(),
4514  PREDEF_DECL_TRANSLATION_UNIT_ID);
4515  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCIdDecl, PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_ID_ID);
4516  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCSelDecl, PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_SEL_ID);
4517  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCClassDecl, PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_CLASS_ID);
4518  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCProtocolClassDecl,
4519  PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_PROTOCOL_ID);
4520  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.Int128Decl, PREDEF_DECL_INT_128_ID);
4521  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.UInt128Decl, PREDEF_DECL_UNSIGNED_INT_128_ID);
4522  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ObjCInstanceTypeDecl,
4523  PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_INSTANCETYPE_ID);
4524  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.BuiltinVaListDecl, PREDEF_DECL_BUILTIN_VA_LIST_ID);
4525  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.VaListTagDecl, PREDEF_DECL_VA_LIST_TAG);
4526  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.BuiltinMSVaListDecl,
4527  PREDEF_DECL_BUILTIN_MS_VA_LIST_ID);
4528  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.MSGuidTagDecl,
4529  PREDEF_DECL_BUILTIN_MS_GUID_ID);
4530  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.ExternCContext, PREDEF_DECL_EXTERN_C_CONTEXT_ID);
4531  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.MakeIntegerSeqDecl,
4532  PREDEF_DECL_MAKE_INTEGER_SEQ_ID);
4533  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.CFConstantStringTypeDecl,
4534  PREDEF_DECL_CF_CONSTANT_STRING_ID);
4535  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.CFConstantStringTagDecl,
4536  PREDEF_DECL_CF_CONSTANT_STRING_TAG_ID);
4537  RegisterPredefDecl(Context.TypePackElementDecl,
4538  PREDEF_DECL_TYPE_PACK_ELEMENT_ID);
4539 
4540  // Build a record containing all of the tentative definitions in this file, in
4541  // TentativeDefinitions order. Generally, this record will be empty for
4542  // headers.
4543  RecordData TentativeDefinitions;
4544  AddLazyVectorDecls(*this, SemaRef.TentativeDefinitions, TentativeDefinitions);
4545 
4546  // Build a record containing all of the file scoped decls in this file.
4547  RecordData UnusedFileScopedDecls;
4548  if (!isModule)
4549  AddLazyVectorDecls(*this, SemaRef.UnusedFileScopedDecls,
4550  UnusedFileScopedDecls);
4551 
4552  // Build a record containing all of the delegating constructors we still need
4553  // to resolve.
4554  RecordData DelegatingCtorDecls;
4555  if (!isModule)
4556  AddLazyVectorDecls(*this, SemaRef.DelegatingCtorDecls, DelegatingCtorDecls);
4557 
4558  // Write the set of weak, undeclared identifiers. We always write the
4559  // entire table, since later PCH files in a PCH chain are only interested in
4560  // the results at the end of the chain.
4561  RecordData WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers;
4562  for (const auto &WeakUndeclaredIdentifierList :
4563  SemaRef.WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers) {
4564  const IdentifierInfo *const II = WeakUndeclaredIdentifierList.first;
4565  for (const auto &WI : WeakUndeclaredIdentifierList.second) {
4566  AddIdentifierRef(II, WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers);
4567  AddIdentifierRef(WI.getAlias(), WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers);
4568  AddSourceLocation(WI.getLocation(), WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers);
4569  }
4570  }
4571 
4572  // Build a record containing all of the ext_vector declarations.
4573  RecordData ExtVectorDecls;
4574  AddLazyVectorDecls(*this, SemaRef.ExtVectorDecls, ExtVectorDecls);
4575 
4576  // Build a record containing all of the VTable uses information.
4577  RecordData VTableUses;
4578  if (!SemaRef.VTableUses.empty()) {
4579  for (unsigned I = 0, N = SemaRef.VTableUses.size(); I != N; ++I) {
4580  AddDeclRef(SemaRef.VTableUses[I].first, VTableUses);
4581  AddSourceLocation(SemaRef.VTableUses[I].second, VTableUses);
4582  VTableUses.push_back(SemaRef.VTablesUsed[SemaRef.VTableUses[I].first]);
4583  }
4584  }
4585 
4586  // Build a record containing all of the UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates.
4587  RecordData UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates;
4588  for (const TypedefNameDecl *TD : SemaRef.UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates)
4589  AddDeclRef(TD, UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates);
4590 
4591  // Build a record containing all of pending implicit instantiations.
4592  RecordData PendingInstantiations;
4593  for (const auto &I : SemaRef.PendingInstantiations) {
4594  AddDeclRef(I.first, PendingInstantiations);
4595  AddSourceLocation(I.second, PendingInstantiations);
4596  }
4597  assert(SemaRef.PendingLocalImplicitInstantiations.empty() &&
4598  "There are local ones at end of translation unit!");
4599 
4600  // Build a record containing some declaration references.
4601  RecordData SemaDeclRefs;
4602  if (SemaRef.StdNamespace || SemaRef.StdBadAlloc || SemaRef.StdAlignValT) {
4603  AddDeclRef(SemaRef.getStdNamespace(), SemaDeclRefs);
4604  AddDeclRef(SemaRef.getStdBadAlloc(), SemaDeclRefs);
4605  AddDeclRef(SemaRef.getStdAlignValT(), SemaDeclRefs);
4606  }
4607 
4608  RecordData CUDASpecialDeclRefs;
4609  if (Context.getcudaConfigureCallDecl()) {
4610  AddDeclRef(Context.getcudaConfigureCallDecl(), CUDASpecialDeclRefs);
4611  }
4612 
4613  // Build a record containing all of the known namespaces.
4614  RecordData KnownNamespaces;
4615  for (const auto &I : SemaRef.KnownNamespaces) {
4616  if (!I.second)
4617  AddDeclRef(I.first, KnownNamespaces);
4618  }
4619 
4620  // Build a record of all used, undefined objects that require definitions.
4621  RecordData UndefinedButUsed;
4622 
4623  SmallVector<std::pair<NamedDecl *, SourceLocation>, 16> Undefined;
4624  SemaRef.getUndefinedButUsed(Undefined);
4625  for (const auto &I : Undefined) {
4626  AddDeclRef(I.first, UndefinedButUsed);
4627  AddSourceLocation(I.second, UndefinedButUsed);
4628  }
4629 
4630  // Build a record containing all delete-expressions that we would like to
4631  // analyze later in AST.
4632  RecordData DeleteExprsToAnalyze;
4633 
4634  if (!isModule) {
4635  for (const auto &DeleteExprsInfo :
4636  SemaRef.getMismatchingDeleteExpressions()) {
4637  AddDeclRef(DeleteExprsInfo.first, DeleteExprsToAnalyze);
4638  DeleteExprsToAnalyze.push_back(DeleteExprsInfo.second.size());
4639  for (const auto &DeleteLoc : DeleteExprsInfo.second) {
4640  AddSourceLocation(DeleteLoc.first, DeleteExprsToAnalyze);
4641  DeleteExprsToAnalyze.push_back(DeleteLoc.second);
4642  }
4643  }
4644  }
4645 
4646  // Write the control block
4647  WriteControlBlock(PP, Context, isysroot, OutputFile);
4648 
4649  // Write the remaining AST contents.
4650  Stream.FlushToWord();
4651  ASTBlockRange.first = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
4652  Stream.EnterSubblock(AST_BLOCK_ID, 5);
4653  ASTBlockStartOffset = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
4654 
4655  // This is so that older clang versions, before the introduction
4656  // of the control block, can read and reject the newer PCH format.
4657  {
4658  RecordData Record = {VERSION_MAJOR};
4659  Stream.EmitRecord(METADATA_OLD_FORMAT, Record);
4660  }
4661 
4662  // Create a lexical update block containing all of the declarations in the
4663  // translation unit that do not come from other AST files.
4664  const TranslationUnitDecl *TU = Context.getTranslationUnitDecl();
4665  SmallVector<uint32_t, 128> NewGlobalKindDeclPairs;
4666  for (const auto *D : TU->noload_decls()) {
4667  if (!D->isFromASTFile()) {
4668  NewGlobalKindDeclPairs.push_back(D->getKind());
4669  NewGlobalKindDeclPairs.push_back(GetDeclRef(D));
4670  }
4671  }
4672 
4673  auto Abv = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
4674  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(TU_UPDATE_LEXICAL));
4675  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
4676  unsigned TuUpdateLexicalAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abv));
4677  {
4678  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {TU_UPDATE_LEXICAL};
4679  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(TuUpdateLexicalAbbrev, Record,
4680  bytes(NewGlobalKindDeclPairs));
4681  }
4682 
4683  // And a visible updates block for the translation unit.
4684  Abv = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
4685  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(UPDATE_VISIBLE));
4686  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::VBR, 6));
4687  Abv->Add(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp(llvm::BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
4688  UpdateVisibleAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abv));
4689  WriteDeclContextVisibleUpdate(TU);
4690 
4691  // If we have any extern "C" names, write out a visible update for them.
4692  if (Context.ExternCContext)
4693  WriteDeclContextVisibleUpdate(Context.ExternCContext);
4694 
4695  // If the translation unit has an anonymous namespace, and we don't already
4696  // have an update block for it, write it as an update block.
4697  // FIXME: Why do we not do this if there's already an update block?
4698  if (NamespaceDecl *NS = TU->getAnonymousNamespace()) {
4699  ASTWriter::UpdateRecord &Record = DeclUpdates[TU];
4700  if (Record.empty())
4701  Record.push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_CXX_ADDED_ANONYMOUS_NAMESPACE, NS));
4702  }
4703 
4704  // Add update records for all mangling numbers and static local numbers.
4705  // These aren't really update records, but this is a convenient way of
4706  // tagging this rare extra data onto the declarations.
4707  for (const auto &Number : Context.MangleNumbers)
4708  if (!Number.first->isFromASTFile())
4709  DeclUpdates[Number.first].push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_MANGLING_NUMBER,
4710  Number.second));
4711  for (const auto &Number : Context.StaticLocalNumbers)
4712  if (!Number.first->isFromASTFile())
4713  DeclUpdates[Number.first].push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_STATIC_LOCAL_NUMBER,
4714  Number.second));
4715 
4716  // Make sure visible decls, added to DeclContexts previously loaded from
4717  // an AST file, are registered for serialization. Likewise for template
4718  // specializations added to imported templates.
4719  for (const auto *I : DeclsToEmitEvenIfUnreferenced) {
4720  GetDeclRef(I);
4721  }
4722 
4723  // Make sure all decls associated with an identifier are registered for
4724  // serialization, if we're storing decls with identifiers.
4725  if (!WritingModule || !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
4726  llvm::SmallVector<const IdentifierInfo*, 256> IIs;
4727  for (const auto &ID : PP.getIdentifierTable()) {
4728  const IdentifierInfo *II = ID.second;
4729  if (!Chain || !II->isFromAST() || II->hasChangedSinceDeserialization())
4730  IIs.push_back(II);
4731  }
4732  // Sort the identifiers to visit based on their name.
4733  llvm::sort(IIs, llvm::deref<std::less<>>());
4734  for (const IdentifierInfo *II : IIs) {
4735  for (IdentifierResolver::iterator D = SemaRef.IdResolver.begin(II),
4736  DEnd = SemaRef.IdResolver.end();
4737  D != DEnd; ++D) {
4738  GetDeclRef(*D);
4739  }
4740  }
4741  }
4742 
4743  // For method pool in the module, if it contains an entry for a selector,
4744  // the entry should be complete, containing everything introduced by that
4745  // module and all modules it imports. It's possible that the entry is out of
4746  // date, so we need to pull in the new content here.
4747 
4748  // It's possible that updateOutOfDateSelector can update SelectorIDs. To be
4749  // safe, we copy all selectors out.
4750  llvm::SmallVector<Selector, 256> AllSelectors;
4751  for (auto &SelectorAndID : SelectorIDs)
4752  AllSelectors.push_back(SelectorAndID.first);
4753  for (auto &Selector : AllSelectors)
4754  SemaRef.updateOutOfDateSelector(Selector);
4755 
4756  // Form the record of special types.
4757  RecordData SpecialTypes;
4758  AddTypeRef(Context.getRawCFConstantStringType(), SpecialTypes);
4759  AddTypeRef(Context.getFILEType(), SpecialTypes);
4760  AddTypeRef(Context.getjmp_bufType(), SpecialTypes);
4761  AddTypeRef(Context.getsigjmp_bufType(), SpecialTypes);
4762  AddTypeRef(Context.ObjCIdRedefinitionType, SpecialTypes);
4763  AddTypeRef(Context.ObjCClassRedefinitionType, SpecialTypes);
4764  AddTypeRef(Context.ObjCSelRedefinitionType, SpecialTypes);
4765  AddTypeRef(Context.getucontext_tType(), SpecialTypes);
4766 
4767  if (Chain) {
4768  // Write the mapping information describing our module dependencies and how
4769  // each of those modules were mapped into our own offset/ID space, so that
4770  // the reader can build the appropriate mapping to its own offset/ID space.
4771  // The map consists solely of a blob with the following format:
4772  // *(module-kind:i8
4773  // module-name-len:i16 module-name:len*i8
4774  // source-location-offset:i32
4775  // identifier-id:i32
4776  // preprocessed-entity-id:i32
4777  // macro-definition-id:i32
4778  // submodule-id:i32
4779  // selector-id:i32
4780  // declaration-id:i32
4781  // c++-base-specifiers-id:i32
4782  // type-id:i32)
4783  //
4784  // module-kind is the ModuleKind enum value. If it is MK_PrebuiltModule,
4785  // MK_ExplicitModule or MK_ImplicitModule, then the module-name is the
4786  // module name. Otherwise, it is the module file name.
4787  auto Abbrev = std::make_shared<BitCodeAbbrev>();
4788  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(MODULE_OFFSET_MAP));
4789  Abbrev->Add(BitCodeAbbrevOp(BitCodeAbbrevOp::Blob));
4790  unsigned ModuleOffsetMapAbbrev = Stream.EmitAbbrev(std::move(Abbrev));
4791  SmallString<2048> Buffer;
4792  {
4793  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Buffer);
4794  for (ModuleFile &M : Chain->ModuleMgr) {
4795  using namespace llvm::support;
4796 
4797  endian::Writer LE(Out, little);
4798  LE.write<uint8_t>(static_cast<uint8_t>(M.Kind));
4799  StringRef Name = M.isModule() ? M.ModuleName : M.FileName;
4800  LE.write<uint16_t>(Name.size());
4801  Out.write(Name.data(), Name.size());
4802 
4803  // Note: if a base ID was uint max, it would not be possible to load
4804  // another module after it or have more than one entity inside it.
4805  uint32_t None = std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max();
4806 
4807  auto writeBaseIDOrNone = [&](auto BaseID, bool ShouldWrite) {
4808  assert(BaseID < std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() && "base id too high");
4809  if (ShouldWrite)
4810  LE.write<uint32_t>(BaseID);
4811  else
4812  LE.write<uint32_t>(None);
4813  };
4814 
4815  // These values should be unique within a chain, since they will be read
4816  // as keys into ContinuousRangeMaps.
4817  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.SLocEntryBaseOffset, M.LocalNumSLocEntries);
4818  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseIdentifierID, M.LocalNumIdentifiers);
4819  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseMacroID, M.LocalNumMacros);
4820  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BasePreprocessedEntityID,
4821  M.NumPreprocessedEntities);
4822  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseSubmoduleID, M.LocalNumSubmodules);
4823  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseSelectorID, M.LocalNumSelectors);
4824  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseDeclID, M.LocalNumDecls);
4825  writeBaseIDOrNone(M.BaseTypeIndex, M.LocalNumTypes);
4826  }
4827  }
4828  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {MODULE_OFFSET_MAP};
4829  Stream.EmitRecordWithBlob(ModuleOffsetMapAbbrev, Record,
4830  Buffer.data(), Buffer.size());
4831  }
4832 
4833  // Build a record containing all of the DeclsToCheckForDeferredDiags.
4834  SmallVector<serialization::DeclID, 64> DeclsToCheckForDeferredDiags;
4835  for (auto *D : SemaRef.DeclsToCheckForDeferredDiags)
4836  DeclsToCheckForDeferredDiags.push_back(GetDeclRef(D));
4837 
4838  RecordData DeclUpdatesOffsetsRecord;
4839 
4840  // Keep writing types, declarations, and declaration update records
4841  // until we've emitted all of them.
4842  Stream.EnterSubblock(DECLTYPES_BLOCK_ID, /*bits for abbreviations*/5);
4843  DeclTypesBlockStartOffset = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
4844  WriteTypeAbbrevs();
4845  WriteDeclAbbrevs();
4846  do {
4847  WriteDeclUpdatesBlocks(DeclUpdatesOffsetsRecord);
4848  while (!DeclTypesToEmit.empty()) {
4849  DeclOrType DOT = DeclTypesToEmit.front();
4850  DeclTypesToEmit.pop();
4851  if (DOT.isType())
4852  WriteType(DOT.getType());
4853  else
4854  WriteDecl(Context, DOT.getDecl());
4855  }
4856  } while (!DeclUpdates.empty());
4857  Stream.ExitBlock();
4858 
4859  DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes = true;
4860 
4861  // These things can only be done once we've written out decls and types.
4862  WriteTypeDeclOffsets();
4863  if (!DeclUpdatesOffsetsRecord.empty())
4864  Stream.EmitRecord(DECL_UPDATE_OFFSETS, DeclUpdatesOffsetsRecord);
4865  WriteFileDeclIDsMap();
4866  WriteSourceManagerBlock(Context.getSourceManager(), PP);
4867  WriteComments();
4868  WritePreprocessor(PP, isModule);
4869  WriteHeaderSearch(PP.getHeaderSearchInfo());
4870  WriteSelectors(SemaRef);
4871  WriteReferencedSelectorsPool(SemaRef);
4872  WriteLateParsedTemplates(SemaRef);
4873  WriteIdentifierTable(PP, SemaRef.IdResolver, isModule);
4874  WriteFPPragmaOptions(SemaRef.CurFPFeatureOverrides());
4875  WriteOpenCLExtensions(SemaRef);
4876  WriteCUDAPragmas(SemaRef);
4877 
4878  // If we're emitting a module, write out the submodule information.
4879  if (WritingModule)
4880  WriteSubmodules(WritingModule);
4881 
4882  Stream.EmitRecord(SPECIAL_TYPES, SpecialTypes);
4883 
4884  // Write the record containing external, unnamed definitions.
4885  if (!EagerlyDeserializedDecls.empty())
4886  Stream.EmitRecord(EAGERLY_DESERIALIZED_DECLS, EagerlyDeserializedDecls);
4887 
4888  if (!ModularCodegenDecls.empty())
4889  Stream.EmitRecord(MODULAR_CODEGEN_DECLS, ModularCodegenDecls);
4890 
4891  // Write the record containing tentative definitions.
4892  if (!TentativeDefinitions.empty())
4893  Stream.EmitRecord(TENTATIVE_DEFINITIONS, TentativeDefinitions);
4894 
4895  // Write the record containing unused file scoped decls.
4896  if (!UnusedFileScopedDecls.empty())
4897  Stream.EmitRecord(UNUSED_FILESCOPED_DECLS, UnusedFileScopedDecls);
4898 
4899  // Write the record containing weak undeclared identifiers.
4900  if (!WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers.empty())
4901  Stream.EmitRecord(WEAK_UNDECLARED_IDENTIFIERS,
4902  WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers);
4903 
4904  // Write the record containing ext_vector type names.
4905  if (!ExtVectorDecls.empty())
4906  Stream.EmitRecord(EXT_VECTOR_DECLS, ExtVectorDecls);
4907 
4908  // Write the record containing VTable uses information.
4909  if (!VTableUses.empty())
4910  Stream.EmitRecord(VTABLE_USES, VTableUses);
4911 
4912  // Write the record containing potentially unused local typedefs.
4913  if (!UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates.empty())
4914  Stream.EmitRecord(UNUSED_LOCAL_TYPEDEF_NAME_CANDIDATES,
4915  UnusedLocalTypedefNameCandidates);
4916 
4917  // Write the record containing pending implicit instantiations.
4918  if (!PendingInstantiations.empty())
4919  Stream.EmitRecord(PENDING_IMPLICIT_INSTANTIATIONS, PendingInstantiations);
4920 
4921  // Write the record containing declaration references of Sema.
4922  if (!SemaDeclRefs.empty())
4923  Stream.EmitRecord(SEMA_DECL_REFS, SemaDeclRefs);
4924 
4925  // Write the record containing decls to be checked for deferred diags.
4926  if (!DeclsToCheckForDeferredDiags.empty())
4927  Stream.EmitRecord(DECLS_TO_CHECK_FOR_DEFERRED_DIAGS,
4928  DeclsToCheckForDeferredDiags);
4929 
4930  // Write the record containing CUDA-specific declaration references.
4931  if (!CUDASpecialDeclRefs.empty())
4932  Stream.EmitRecord(CUDA_SPECIAL_DECL_REFS, CUDASpecialDeclRefs);
4933 
4934  // Write the delegating constructors.
4935  if (!DelegatingCtorDecls.empty())
4936  Stream.EmitRecord(DELEGATING_CTORS, DelegatingCtorDecls);
4937 
4938  // Write the known namespaces.
4939  if (!KnownNamespaces.empty())
4940  Stream.EmitRecord(KNOWN_NAMESPACES, KnownNamespaces);
4941 
4942  // Write the undefined internal functions and variables, and inline functions.
4943  if (!UndefinedButUsed.empty())
4944  Stream.EmitRecord(UNDEFINED_BUT_USED, UndefinedButUsed);
4945 
4946  if (!DeleteExprsToAnalyze.empty())
4947  Stream.EmitRecord(DELETE_EXPRS_TO_ANALYZE, DeleteExprsToAnalyze);
4948 
4949  // Write the visible updates to DeclContexts.
4950  for (auto *DC : UpdatedDeclContexts)
4951  WriteDeclContextVisibleUpdate(DC);
4952 
4953  if (!WritingModule) {
4954  // Write the submodules that were imported, if any.
4955  struct ModuleInfo {
4956  uint64_t ID;
4957  Module *M;
4958  ModuleInfo(uint64_t ID, Module *M) : ID(ID), M(M) {}
4959  };
4960  llvm::SmallVector<ModuleInfo, 64> Imports;
4961  for (const auto *I : Context.local_imports()) {
4962  assert(SubmoduleIDs.find(I->getImportedModule()) != SubmoduleIDs.end());
4963  Imports.push_back(ModuleInfo(SubmoduleIDs[I->getImportedModule()],
4964  I->getImportedModule()));
4965  }
4966 
4967  if (!Imports.empty()) {
4968  auto Cmp = [](const ModuleInfo &A, const ModuleInfo &B) {
4969  return A.ID < B.ID;
4970  };
4971  auto Eq = [](const ModuleInfo &A, const ModuleInfo &B) {
4972  return A.ID == B.ID;
4973  };
4974 
4975  // Sort and deduplicate module IDs.
4976  llvm::sort(Imports, Cmp);
4977  Imports.erase(std::unique(Imports.begin(), Imports.end(), Eq),
4978  Imports.end());
4979 
4980  RecordData ImportedModules;
4981  for (const auto &Import : Imports) {
4982  ImportedModules.push_back(Import.ID);
4983  // FIXME: If the module has macros imported then later has declarations
4984  // imported, this location won't be the right one as a location for the
4985  // declaration imports.
4986  AddSourceLocation(PP.getModuleImportLoc(Import.M), ImportedModules);
4987  }
4988 
4989  Stream.EmitRecord(IMPORTED_MODULES, ImportedModules);
4990  }
4991  }
4992 
4993  WriteObjCCategories();
4994  if(!WritingModule) {
4995  WriteOptimizePragmaOptions(SemaRef);
4996  WriteMSStructPragmaOptions(SemaRef);
4997  WriteMSPointersToMembersPragmaOptions(SemaRef);
4998  }
4999  WritePackPragmaOptions(SemaRef);
5000  WriteFloatControlPragmaOptions(SemaRef);
5001 
5002  // Some simple statistics
5003  RecordData::value_type Record[] = {
5004  NumStatements, NumMacros, NumLexicalDeclContexts, NumVisibleDeclContexts};
5005  Stream.EmitRecord(STATISTICS, Record);
5006  Stream.ExitBlock();
5007  Stream.FlushToWord();
5008  ASTBlockRange.second = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
5009 
5010  // Write the module file extension blocks.
5011  for (const auto &ExtWriter : ModuleFileExtensionWriters)
5012  WriteModuleFileExtension(SemaRef, *ExtWriter);
5013 
5014  return writeUnhashedControlBlock(PP, Context);
5015 }
5016 
5017 void ASTWriter::WriteDeclUpdatesBlocks(RecordDataImpl &OffsetsRecord) {
5018  if (DeclUpdates.empty())
5019  return;
5020 
5021  DeclUpdateMap LocalUpdates;
5022  LocalUpdates.swap(DeclUpdates);
5023 
5024  for (auto &DeclUpdate : LocalUpdates) {
5025  const Decl *D = DeclUpdate.first;
5026 
5027  bool HasUpdatedBody = false;
5028  RecordData RecordData;
5029  ASTRecordWriter Record(*this, RecordData);
5030  for (auto &Update : DeclUpdate.second) {
5031  DeclUpdateKind Kind = (DeclUpdateKind)Update.getKind();
5032 
5033  // An updated body is emitted last, so that the reader doesn't need
5034  // to skip over the lazy body to reach statements for other records.
5035  if (Kind == UPD_CXX_ADDED_FUNCTION_DEFINITION)
5036  HasUpdatedBody = true;
5037  else
5038  Record.push_back(Kind);
5039 
5040  switch (Kind) {
5041  case UPD_CXX_ADDED_IMPLICIT_MEMBER:
5042  case UPD_CXX_ADDED_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION:
5043  case UPD_CXX_ADDED_ANONYMOUS_NAMESPACE:
5044  assert(Update.getDecl() && "no decl to add?");
5045  Record.push_back(GetDeclRef(Update.getDecl()));
5046  break;
5047 
5048  case UPD_CXX_ADDED_FUNCTION_DEFINITION:
5049  break;
5050 
5051  case UPD_CXX_POINT_OF_INSTANTIATION:
5052  // FIXME: Do we need to also save the template specialization kind here?
5053  Record.AddSourceLocation(Update.getLoc());
5054  break;
5055 
5056  case UPD_CXX_ADDED_VAR_DEFINITION: {
5057  const VarDecl *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
5058  Record.push_back(VD->isInline());
5059  Record.push_back(VD->isInlineSpecified());
5060  Record.AddVarDeclInit(VD);
5061  break;
5062  }
5063 
5064  case UPD_CXX_INSTANTIATED_DEFAULT_ARGUMENT:
5065  Record.AddStmt(const_cast<Expr *>(
5066  cast<ParmVarDecl>(Update.getDecl())->getDefaultArg()));
5067  break;
5068 
5069  case UPD_CXX_INSTANTIATED_DEFAULT_MEMBER_INITIALIZER:
5070  Record.AddStmt(
5071  cast<FieldDecl>(Update.getDecl())->getInClassInitializer());
5072  break;
5073 
5074  case UPD_CXX_INSTANTIATED_CLASS_DEFINITION: {
5075  auto *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
5076  UpdatedDeclContexts.insert(RD->getPrimaryContext());
5077  Record.push_back(RD->isParamDestroyedInCallee());
5078  Record.push_back(RD->getArgPassingRestrictions());
5079  Record.AddCXXDefinitionData(RD);
5080  Record.AddOffset(WriteDeclContextLexicalBlock(
5081  *Context, const_cast<CXXRecordDecl *>(RD)));
5082 
5083  // This state is sometimes updated by template instantiation, when we
5084  // switch from the specialization referring to the template declaration
5085  // to it referring to the template definition.
5086  if (auto *MSInfo = RD->getMemberSpecializationInfo()) {
5087  Record.push_back(MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind());
5088  Record.AddSourceLocation(MSInfo->getPointOfInstantiation());
5089  } else {
5090  auto *Spec = cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD);
5091  Record.push_back(Spec->getTemplateSpecializationKind());
5092  Record.AddSourceLocation(Spec->getPointOfInstantiation());
5093 
5094  // The instantiation might have been resolved to a partial
5095  // specialization. If so, record which one.
5096  auto From = Spec->getInstantiatedFrom();
5097  if (auto PartialSpec =
5098  From.dyn_cast<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl*>()) {
5099  Record.push_back(true);
5100  Record.AddDeclRef(PartialSpec);
5101  Record.AddTemplateArgumentList(
5102  &Spec->getTemplateInstantiationArgs());
5103  } else {
5104  Record.push_back(false);
5105  }
5106  }
5107  Record.push_back(RD->getTagKind());
5108  Record.AddSourceLocation(RD->getLocation());
5109  Record.AddSourceLocation(RD->getBeginLoc());
5110  Record.AddSourceRange(RD->getBraceRange());
5111 
5112  // Instantiation may change attributes; write them all out afresh.
5113  Record.push_back(D->hasAttrs());
5114  if (D->hasAttrs())
5115  Record.AddAttributes(D->getAttrs());
5116 
5117  // FIXME: Ensure we don't get here for explicit instantiations.
5118  break;
5119  }
5120 
5121  case UPD_CXX_RESOLVED_DTOR_DELETE:
5122  Record.AddDeclRef(Update.getDecl());
5123  Record.AddStmt(cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D)->getOperatorDeleteThisArg());
5124  break;
5125 
5126  case UPD_CXX_RESOLVED_EXCEPTION_SPEC: {
5127  auto prototype =
5128  cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
5129  Record.writeExceptionSpecInfo(prototype->getExceptionSpecInfo());
5130  break;
5131  }
5132 
5133  case UPD_CXX_DEDUCED_RETURN_TYPE:
5134  Record.push_back(GetOrCreateTypeID(Update.getType()));
5135  break;
5136 
5137  case UPD_DECL_MARKED_USED:
5138  break;
5139 
5140  case UPD_MANGLING_NUMBER:
5141  case UPD_STATIC_LOCAL_NUMBER:
5142  Record.push_back(Update.getNumber());
5143  break;
5144 
5145  case UPD_DECL_MARKED_OPENMP_THREADPRIVATE:
5146  Record.AddSourceRange(
5147  D->getAttr<OMPThreadPrivateDeclAttr>()->getRange());
5148  break;
5149 
5150  case UPD_DECL_MARKED_OPENMP_ALLOCATE: {
5151  auto *A = D->getAttr<OMPAllocateDeclAttr>();
5152  Record.push_back(A->getAllocatorType());
5153  Record.AddStmt(A->getAllocator());
5154  Record.AddStmt(A->getAlignment());
5155  Record.AddSourceRange(A->getRange());
5156  break;
5157  }
5158 
5159  case UPD_DECL_MARKED_OPENMP_DECLARETARGET:
5160  Record.push_back(D->getAttr<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr>()->getMapType());
5161  Record.AddSourceRange(
5162  D->getAttr<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr>()->getRange());
5163  break;
5164 
5165  case UPD_DECL_EXPORTED:
5166  Record.push_back(getSubmoduleID(Update.getModule()));
5167  break;
5168 
5169  case UPD_ADDED_ATTR_TO_RECORD:
5170  Record.AddAttributes(llvm::makeArrayRef(Update.getAttr()));
5171  break;
5172  }
5173  }
5174 
5175  if (HasUpdatedBody) {
5176  const auto *Def = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
5177  Record.push_back(UPD_CXX_ADDED_FUNCTION_DEFINITION);
5178  Record.push_back(Def->isInlined());
5179  Record.AddSourceLocation(Def->getInnerLocStart());
5180  Record.AddFunctionDefinition(Def);
5181  }
5182 
5183  OffsetsRecord.push_back(GetDeclRef(D));
5184  OffsetsRecord.push_back(Record.Emit(DECL_UPDATES));
5185  }
5186 }

5196  Record.push_back((Raw << 1) | (Raw >> (8 * sizeof(Raw) - 1)));
5197 }

5222 MacroID ASTWriter::getMacroRef(MacroInfo *MI, const IdentifierInfo *Name) {
5223  // Don't emit builtin macros like __LINE__ to the AST file unless they
5224  // have been redefined by the header (in which case they are not
5225  // isBuiltinMacro).
5226  if (!MI || MI->isBuiltinMacro())
5227  return 0;
5228 
5229  MacroID &ID = MacroIDs[MI];
5230  if (ID == 0) {
5231  ID = NextMacroID++;
5232  MacroInfoToEmitData Info = { Name, MI, ID };
5233  MacroInfosToEmit.push_back(Info);
5234  }
5235  return ID;
5236 }

5240  return 0;
5241 
5242  assert(MacroIDs.find(MI) != MacroIDs.end() && "Macro not emitted!");
5243  return MacroIDs[MI];
5244 }

5253 
5254 SelectorID ASTWriter::getSelectorRef(Selector Sel) {
5255  if (Sel.getAsOpaquePtr() == nullptr) {
5256  return 0;
5257  }
5258 
5259  SelectorID SID = SelectorIDs[Sel];
5260  if (SID == 0 && Chain) {
5261  // This might trigger a ReadSelector callback, which will set the ID for
5262  // this selector.
5263  Chain->LoadSelector(Sel);
5264  SID = SelectorIDs[Sel];
5265  }
5266  if (SID == 0) {
5267  SID = NextSelectorID++;
5268  SelectorIDs[Sel] = SID;
5269  }
5270  return SID;
5271 }

5277 void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateArgumentLocInfo(
5278  TemplateArgument::ArgKind Kind, const TemplateArgumentLocInfo &Arg) {
5279  switch (Kind) {
5280  case TemplateArgument::Expression:
5281  AddStmt(Arg.getAsExpr());
5282  break;
5283  case TemplateArgument::Type:
5284  AddTypeSourceInfo(Arg.getAsTypeSourceInfo());
5285  break;
5286  case TemplateArgument::Template:
5287  AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(Arg.getTemplateQualifierLoc());
5288  AddSourceLocation(Arg.getTemplateNameLoc());
5289  break;
5290  case TemplateArgument::TemplateExpansion:
5291  AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(Arg.getTemplateQualifierLoc());
5292  AddSourceLocation(Arg.getTemplateNameLoc());
5293  AddSourceLocation(Arg.getTemplateEllipsisLoc());
5294  break;
5295  case TemplateArgument::Null:
5296  case TemplateArgument::Integral:
5297  case TemplateArgument::Declaration:
5298  case TemplateArgument::NullPtr:
5299  case TemplateArgument::Pack:
5300  // FIXME: Is this right?
5301  break;
5302  }
5303 }

5305 void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateArgumentLoc(const TemplateArgumentLoc &Arg) {
5306  AddTemplateArgument(Arg.getArgument());
5307 
5308  if (Arg.getArgument().getKind() == TemplateArgument::Expression) {
5309  bool InfoHasSameExpr
5310  = Arg.getArgument().getAsExpr() == Arg.getLocInfo().getAsExpr();
5311  Record->push_back(InfoHasSameExpr);
5312  if (InfoHasSameExpr)
5313  return; // Avoid storing the same expr twice.
5314  }
5315  AddTemplateArgumentLocInfo(Arg.getArgument().getKind(), Arg.getLocInfo());
5316 }

5337 
5338 TypeID ASTWriter::GetOrCreateTypeID(QualType T) {
5339  assert(Context);
5340  return MakeTypeID(*Context, T, [&](QualType T) -> TypeIdx {
5341  if (T.isNull())
5342  return TypeIdx();
5343  assert(!T.getLocalFastQualifiers());
5344 
5345  TypeIdx &Idx = TypeIdxs[T];
5346  if (Idx.getIndex() == 0) {
5347  if (DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes) {
5348  assert(0 && "New type seen after serializing all the types to emit!");
5349  return TypeIdx();
5350  }
5351 
5352  // We haven't seen this type before. Assign it a new ID and put it
5353  // into the queue of types to emit.
5354  Idx = TypeIdx(NextTypeID++);
5355  DeclTypesToEmit.push(T);
5356  }
5357  return Idx;
5358  });
5359 }
5360 
5361 TypeID ASTWriter::getTypeID(QualType T) const {
5362  assert(Context);
5363  return MakeTypeID(*Context, T, [&](QualType T) -> TypeIdx {
5364  if (T.isNull())
5365  return TypeIdx();
5366  assert(!T.getLocalFastQualifiers());
5367 
5368  TypeIdxMap::const_iterator I = TypeIdxs.find(T);
5369  assert(I != TypeIdxs.end() && "Type not emitted!");
5370  return I->second;
5371  });
5372 }

5376 }
5377 
5378 DeclID ASTWriter::GetDeclRef(const Decl *D) {
5379  assert(WritingAST && "Cannot request a declaration ID before AST writing");
5380 
5381  if (!D) {
5382  return 0;
5383  }
5384 
5385  // If D comes from an AST file, its declaration ID is already known and
5386  // fixed.
5387  if (D->isFromASTFile())
5388  return D->getGlobalID();
5389 
5390  assert(!(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(D) & 0x01) && "Invalid decl pointer");
5391  DeclID &ID = DeclIDs[D];
5392  if (ID == 0) {
5393  if (DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes) {
5394  assert(0 && "New decl seen after serializing all the decls to emit!");
5395  return 0;
5396  }
5397 
5398  // We haven't seen this declaration before. Give it a new ID and
5399  // enqueue it in the list of declarations to emit.
5400  ID = NextDeclID++;
5401  DeclTypesToEmit.push(const_cast<Decl *>(D));
5402  }
5403 
5404  return ID;
5405 }
5406 
5407 DeclID ASTWriter::getDeclID(const Decl *D) {
5408  if (!D)
5409  return 0;
5410 
5411  // If D comes from an AST file, its declaration ID is already known and
5412  // fixed.
5413  if (D->isFromASTFile())
5414  return D->getGlobalID();
5415 
5416  assert(DeclIDs.find(D) != DeclIDs.end() && "Declaration not emitted!");
5417  return DeclIDs[D];
5418 }
5419 
5420 void ASTWriter::associateDeclWithFile(const Decl *D, DeclID ID) {
5421  assert(ID);
5422  assert(D);
5423 
5424  SourceLocation Loc = D->getLocation();
5425  if (Loc.isInvalid())
5426  return;
5427 
5428  // We only keep track of the file-level declarations of each file.
5429  if (!D->getLexicalDeclContext()->isFileContext())
5430  return;
5431  // FIXME: ParmVarDecls that are part of a function type of a parameter of
5432  // a function/objc method, should not have TU as lexical context.
5433  // TemplateTemplateParmDecls that are part of an alias template, should not
5434  // have TU as lexical context.
5435  if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(D) || isa<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(D))
5436  return;
5437 
5438  SourceManager &SM = Context->getSourceManager();
5439  SourceLocation FileLoc = SM.getFileLoc(Loc);
5440  assert(SM.isLocalSourceLocation(FileLoc));
5441  FileID FID;
5442  unsigned Offset;
5443  std::tie(FID, Offset) = SM.getDecomposedLoc(FileLoc);
5444  if (FID.isInvalid())
5445  return;
5446  assert(SM.getSLocEntry(FID).isFile());
5447 
5448  std::unique_ptr<DeclIDInFileInfo> &Info = FileDeclIDs[FID];
5449  if (!Info)
5450  Info = std::make_unique<DeclIDInFileInfo>();
5451 
5452  std::pair<unsigned, serialization::DeclID> LocDecl(Offset, ID);
5453  LocDeclIDsTy &Decls = Info->DeclIDs;
5454 
5455  if (Decls.empty() || Decls.back().first <= Offset) {
5456  Decls.push_back(LocDecl);
5457  return;
5458  }
5459 
5460  LocDeclIDsTy::iterator I =
5461  llvm::upper_bound(Decls, LocDecl, llvm::less_first());
5462 
5463  Decls.insert(I, LocDecl);
5464 }
5465 
5466 unsigned ASTWriter::getAnonymousDeclarationNumber(const NamedDecl *D) {
5467  assert(needsAnonymousDeclarationNumber(D) &&
5468  "expected an anonymous declaration");
5469 
5470  // Number the anonymous declarations within this context, if we've not
5471  // already done so.
5472  auto It = AnonymousDeclarationNumbers.find(D);
5473  if (It == AnonymousDeclarationNumbers.end()) {
5474  auto *DC = D->getLexicalDeclContext();
5475  numberAnonymousDeclsWithin(DC, [&](const NamedDecl *ND, unsigned Number) {
5476  AnonymousDeclarationNumbers[ND] = Number;
5477  });
5478 
5479  It = AnonymousDeclarationNumbers.find(D);
5480  assert(It != AnonymousDeclarationNumbers.end() &&
5481  "declaration not found within its lexical context");
5482  }
5483 
5484  return It->second;
5485 }

5487 void ASTRecordWriter::AddDeclarationNameLoc(const DeclarationNameLoc &DNLoc,
5488  DeclarationName Name) {
5489  switch (Name.getNameKind()) {
5490  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
5491  case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName:
5492  case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName:
5493  AddTypeSourceInfo(DNLoc.getNamedTypeInfo());
5494  break;
5495 
5496  case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName:
5497  AddSourceRange(DNLoc.getCXXOperatorNameRange());
5498  break;
5499 
5500  case DeclarationName::CXXLiteralOperatorName:
5501  AddSourceLocation(DNLoc.getCXXLiteralOperatorNameLoc());
5502  break;
5503 
5504  case DeclarationName::Identifier:
5505  case DeclarationName::ObjCZeroArgSelector:
5506  case DeclarationName::ObjCOneArgSelector:
5507  case DeclarationName::ObjCMultiArgSelector:
5508  case DeclarationName::CXXUsingDirective:
5509  case DeclarationName::CXXDeductionGuideName:
5510  break;
5511  }
5512 }

5521 void ASTRecordWriter::AddQualifierInfo(const QualifierInfo &Info) {
5522  AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(Info.QualifierLoc);
5523  Record->push_back(Info.NumTemplParamLists);
5524  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Info.NumTemplParamLists; i != e; ++i)
5525  AddTemplateParameterList(Info.TemplParamLists[i]);

5527 
5528 void ASTRecordWriter::AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(NestedNameSpecifierLoc NNS) {
5529  // Nested name specifiers usually aren't too long. I think that 8 would
5530  // typically accommodate the vast majority.
5531  SmallVector<NestedNameSpecifierLoc , 8> NestedNames;
5532 
5533  // Push each of the nested-name-specifiers's onto a stack for
5534  // serialization in reverse order.
5535  while (NNS) {
5536  NestedNames.push_back(NNS);
5537  NNS = NNS.getPrefix();
5538  }
5539 
5540  Record->push_back(NestedNames.size());
5541  while(!NestedNames.empty()) {
5542  NNS = NestedNames.pop_back_val();
5543  NestedNameSpecifier::SpecifierKind Kind
5544  = NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getKind();
5545  Record->push_back(Kind);
5546  switch (Kind) {
5547  case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
5548  AddIdentifierRef(NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getAsIdentifier());
5549  AddSourceRange(NNS.getLocalSourceRange());
5550  break;
5551 
5552  case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
5553  AddDeclRef(NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getAsNamespace());
5554  AddSourceRange(NNS.getLocalSourceRange());
5555  break;
5556 
5557  case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
5558  AddDeclRef(NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getAsNamespaceAlias());
5559  AddSourceRange(NNS.getLocalSourceRange());
5560  break;
5561 
5562  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
5563  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
5564  Record->push_back(Kind == NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate);
5565  AddTypeRef(NNS.getTypeLoc().getType());
5566  AddTypeLoc(NNS.getTypeLoc());
5567  AddSourceLocation(NNS.getLocalSourceRange().getEnd());
5568  break;
5569 
5570  case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
5571  AddSourceLocation(NNS.getLocalSourceRange().getEnd());
5572  break;
5573 
5574  case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
5575  AddDeclRef(NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getAsRecordDecl());
5576  AddSourceRange(NNS.getLocalSourceRange());
5577  break;
5578  }
5579  }
5580 }
5581 
5582 void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateParameterList(
5583  const TemplateParameterList *TemplateParams) {
5584  assert(TemplateParams && "No TemplateParams!");
5585  AddSourceLocation(TemplateParams->getTemplateLoc());
5586  AddSourceLocation(TemplateParams->getLAngleLoc());
5587  AddSourceLocation(TemplateParams->getRAngleLoc());
5588 
5589  Record->push_back(TemplateParams->size());
5590  for (const auto &P : *TemplateParams)
5591  AddDeclRef(P);
5592  if (const Expr *RequiresClause = TemplateParams->getRequiresClause()) {
5593  Record->push_back(true);
5594  AddStmt(const_cast<Expr*>(RequiresClause));
5595  } else {
5596  Record->push_back(false);
5597  }
5598 }
5599 
5600 /// Emit a template argument list.
5601 void ASTRecordWriter::AddTemplateArgumentList(
5602  const TemplateArgumentList *TemplateArgs) {
5603  assert(TemplateArgs && "No TemplateArgs!");
5604  Record->push_back(TemplateArgs->size());
5605  for (int i = 0, e = TemplateArgs->size(); i != e; ++i)
5606  AddTemplateArgument(TemplateArgs->get(i));
5607 }
5608 
5609 void ASTRecordWriter::AddASTTemplateArgumentListInfo(
5610  const ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo *ASTTemplArgList) {
5611  assert(ASTTemplArgList && "No ASTTemplArgList!");
5612  AddSourceLocation(ASTTemplArgList->LAngleLoc);
5613  AddSourceLocation(ASTTemplArgList->RAngleLoc);
5614  Record->push_back(ASTTemplArgList->NumTemplateArgs);
5615  const TemplateArgumentLoc *TemplArgs = ASTTemplArgList->getTemplateArgs();
5616  for (int i = 0, e = ASTTemplArgList->NumTemplateArgs; i != e; ++i)
5617  AddTemplateArgumentLoc(TemplArgs[i]);
5618 }
5619 
5620 void ASTRecordWriter::AddUnresolvedSet(const ASTUnresolvedSet &Set) {
5621  Record->push_back(Set.size());
5622  for (ASTUnresolvedSet::const_iterator
5623  I = Set.begin(), E = Set.end(); I != E; ++I) {
5624  AddDeclRef(I.getDecl());
5625  Record->push_back(I.getAccess());
5626  }
5627 }
5628 
5629 // FIXME: Move this out of the main ASTRecordWriter interface.
5630 void ASTRecordWriter::AddCXXBaseSpecifier(const CXXBaseSpecifier &Base) {
5631  Record->push_back(Base.isVirtual());
5632  Record->push_back(Base.isBaseOfClass());
5633  Record->push_back(Base.getAccessSpecifierAsWritten());
5634  Record->push_back(Base.getInheritConstructors());
5635  AddTypeSourceInfo(Base.getTypeSourceInfo());
5636  AddSourceRange(Base.getSourceRange());
5637  AddSourceLocation(Base.isPackExpansion()? Base.getEllipsisLoc()
5638  : SourceLocation());
5639 }
5640 
5641 static uint64_t EmitCXXBaseSpecifiers(ASTWriter &W,
5642  ArrayRef<CXXBaseSpecifier> Bases) {
5643  ASTWriter::RecordData Record;
5644  ASTRecordWriter Writer(W, Record);
5645  Writer.push_back(Bases.size());
5646 
5647  for (auto &Base : Bases)
5648  Writer.AddCXXBaseSpecifier(Base);
5649 
5650  return Writer.Emit(serialization::DECL_CXX_BASE_SPECIFIERS);
5651 }
5652 
5653 // FIXME: Move this out of the main ASTRecordWriter interface.
5654 void ASTRecordWriter::AddCXXBaseSpecifiers(ArrayRef<CXXBaseSpecifier> Bases) {
5655  AddOffset(EmitCXXBaseSpecifiers(*Writer, Bases));
5656 }
5657 
5658 static uint64_t
5659 EmitCXXCtorInitializers(ASTWriter &W,
5660  ArrayRef<CXXCtorInitializer *> CtorInits) {
5661  ASTWriter::RecordData Record;
5662  ASTRecordWriter Writer(W, Record);
5663  Writer.push_back(CtorInits.size());
5664 
5665  for (auto *Init : CtorInits) {
5666  if (Init->isBaseInitializer()) {
5667  Writer.push_back(CTOR_INITIALIZER_BASE);
5668  Writer.AddTypeSourceInfo(Init->getTypeSourceInfo());
5669  Writer.push_back(Init->isBaseVirtual());
5670  } else if (Init->isDelegatingInitializer()) {
5671  Writer.push_back(CTOR_INITIALIZER_DELEGATING);
5672  Writer.AddTypeSourceInfo(Init->getTypeSourceInfo());
5673  } else if (Init->isMemberInitializer()){
5674  Writer.push_back(CTOR_INITIALIZER_MEMBER);
5675  Writer.AddDeclRef(Init->getMember());
5676  } else {
5677  Writer.push_back(CTOR_INITIALIZER_INDIRECT_MEMBER);
5678  Writer.AddDeclRef(Init->getIndirectMember());
5679  }
5680 
5681  Writer.AddSourceLocation(Init->getMemberLocation());
5682  Writer.AddStmt(Init->getInit());
5683  Writer.AddSourceLocation(Init->getLParenLoc());
5684  Writer.AddSourceLocation(Init->getRParenLoc());
5685  Writer.push_back(Init->isWritten());
5686  if (Init->isWritten())
5687  Writer.push_back(Init->getSourceOrder());
5688  }
5689 
5690  return Writer.Emit(serialization::DECL_CXX_CTOR_INITIALIZERS);
5691 }
5692 
5693 // FIXME: Move this out of the main ASTRecordWriter interface.
5694 void ASTRecordWriter::AddCXXCtorInitializers(
5695  ArrayRef<CXXCtorInitializer *> CtorInits) {
5696  AddOffset(EmitCXXCtorInitializers(*Writer, CtorInits));
5697 }
5698 
5699 void ASTRecordWriter::AddCXXDefinitionData(const CXXRecordDecl *D) {
5700  auto &Data = D->data();
5701  Record->push_back(Data.IsLambda);
5702 
5703  #define FIELD(Name, Width, Merge) \
5704  Record->push_back(Data.Name);
5705  #include "clang/AST/CXXRecordDeclDefinitionBits.def"
5706 
5707  // getODRHash will compute the ODRHash if it has not been previously computed.
5708  Record->push_back(D->getODRHash());
5709  bool ModulesDebugInfo =
5710  Writer->Context->getLangOpts().ModulesDebugInfo && !D->isDependentType();
5711  Record->push_back(ModulesDebugInfo);
5712  if (ModulesDebugInfo)
5713  Writer->ModularCodegenDecls.push_back(Writer->GetDeclRef(D));
5714 
5715  // IsLambda bit is already saved.
5716 
5717  Record->push_back(Data.NumBases);
5718  if (Data.NumBases > 0)
5719  AddCXXBaseSpecifiers(Data.bases());
5720 
5721  // FIXME: Make VBases lazily computed when needed to avoid storing them.
5722  Record->push_back(Data.NumVBases);
5723  if (Data.NumVBases > 0)
5724  AddCXXBaseSpecifiers(Data.vbases());
5725 
5726  AddUnresolvedSet(Data.Conversions.get(*Writer->Context));
5727  Record->push_back(Data.ComputedVisibleConversions);
5728  if (Data.ComputedVisibleConversions)
5729  AddUnresolvedSet(Data.VisibleConversions.get(*Writer->Context));
5730  // Data.Definition is the owning decl, no need to write it.
5731  AddDeclRef(D->getFirstFriend());
5732 
5733  // Add lambda-specific data.
5734  if (Data.IsLambda) {
5735  auto &Lambda = D->getLambdaData();
5736  Record->push_back(Lambda.DependencyKind);
5737  Record->push_back(Lambda.IsGenericLambda);
5738  Record->push_back(Lambda.CaptureDefault);
5739  Record->push_back(Lambda.NumCaptures);
5740  Record->push_back(Lambda.NumExplicitCaptures);
5741  Record->push_back(Lambda.HasKnownInternalLinkage);
5742  Record->push_back(Lambda.ManglingNumber);
5743  Record->push_back(D->getDeviceLambdaManglingNumber());
5744  AddDeclRef(D->getLambdaContextDecl());
5745  AddTypeSourceInfo(Lambda.MethodTyInfo);
5746  for (unsigned I = 0, N = Lambda.NumCaptures; I != N; ++I) {
5747  const LambdaCapture &Capture = Lambda.Captures[I];
5748  AddSourceLocation(Capture.getLocation());
5749  Record->push_back(Capture.isImplicit());
5750  Record->push_back(Capture.getCaptureKind());
5751  switch (Capture.getCaptureKind()) {
5752  case LCK_StarThis:
5753  case LCK_This:
5754  case LCK_VLAType:
5755  break;
5756  case LCK_ByCopy:
5757  case LCK_ByRef:
5758  VarDecl *Var =
5759  Capture.capturesVariable() ? Capture.getCapturedVar() : nullptr;
5760  AddDeclRef(Var);
5761  AddSourceLocation(Capture.isPackExpansion() ? Capture.getEllipsisLoc()
5762  : SourceLocation());
5763  break;
5764  }
5765  }
5766  }
5767 }
5768 
5769 void ASTRecordWriter::AddVarDeclInit(const VarDecl *VD) {
5770  const Expr *Init = VD->getInit();
5771  if (!Init) {
5772  push_back(0);
5773  return;
5774  }
5775 
5776  unsigned Val = 1;
5777  if (EvaluatedStmt *ES = VD->getEvaluatedStmt()) {
5778  Val |= (ES->HasConstantInitialization ? 2 : 0);
5779  Val |= (ES->HasConstantDestruction ? 4 : 0);
5780  // FIXME: Also emit the constant initializer value.
5781  }
5782  push_back(Val);
5783  writeStmtRef(Init);
5784 }
5785 
5786 void ASTWriter::ReaderInitialized(ASTReader *Reader) {
5787  assert(Reader && "Cannot remove chain");
5788  assert((!Chain || Chain == Reader) && "Cannot replace chain");
5789  assert(FirstDeclID == NextDeclID &&
5790  FirstTypeID == NextTypeID &&
5791  FirstIdentID == NextIdentID &&
5792  FirstMacroID == NextMacroID &&
5793  FirstSubmoduleID == NextSubmoduleID &&
5794  FirstSelectorID == NextSelectorID &&
5795  "Setting chain after writing has started.");
5796 
5797  Chain = Reader;
5798 
5799  // Note, this will get called multiple times, once one the reader starts up
5800  // and again each time it's done reading a PCH or module.
5801  FirstDeclID = NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumDecls();
5802  FirstTypeID = NUM_PREDEF_TYPE_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumTypes();
5803  FirstIdentID = NUM_PREDEF_IDENT_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumIdentifiers();
5804  FirstMacroID = NUM_PREDEF_MACRO_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumMacros();
5805  FirstSubmoduleID = NUM_PREDEF_SUBMODULE_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumSubmodules();
5806  FirstSelectorID = NUM_PREDEF_SELECTOR_IDS + Chain->getTotalNumSelectors();
5807  NextDeclID = FirstDeclID;
5808  NextTypeID = FirstTypeID;
5809  NextIdentID = FirstIdentID;
5810  NextMacroID = FirstMacroID;
5811  NextSelectorID = FirstSelectorID;
5812  NextSubmoduleID = FirstSubmoduleID;
5813 }
5814 
5815 void ASTWriter::IdentifierRead(IdentID ID, IdentifierInfo *II) {
5816  // Always keep the highest ID. See \p TypeRead() for more information.
5817  IdentID &StoredID = IdentifierIDs[II];
5818  if (ID > StoredID)
5819  StoredID = ID;
5820 }
5821 
5822 void ASTWriter::MacroRead(serialization::MacroID ID, MacroInfo *MI) {
5823  // Always keep the highest ID. See \p TypeRead() for more information.
5824  MacroID &StoredID = MacroIDs[MI];
5825  if (ID > StoredID)
5826  StoredID = ID;
5827 }
5828 
5829 void ASTWriter::TypeRead(TypeIdx Idx, QualType T) {
5830  // Always take the highest-numbered type index. This copes with an interesting
5831  // case for chained AST writing where we schedule writing the type and then,
5832  // later, deserialize the type from another AST. In this case, we want to
5833  // keep the higher-numbered entry so that we can properly write it out to
5834  // the AST file.
5835  TypeIdx &StoredIdx = TypeIdxs[T];
5836  if (Idx.getIndex() >= StoredIdx.getIndex())
5837  StoredIdx = Idx;
5838 }
5839 
5840 void ASTWriter::SelectorRead(SelectorID ID, Selector S) {
5841  // Always keep the highest ID. See \p TypeRead() for more information.
5842  SelectorID &StoredID = SelectorIDs[S];
5843  if (ID > StoredID)
5844  StoredID = ID;
5845 }

5850  MacroDefinitions[MD] = ID;
5851 }

5858 void ASTWriter::CompletedTagDefinition(const TagDecl *D) {
5859  if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
5860  assert(D->isCompleteDefinition());
5861  assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
5862  if (auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
5863  // We are interested when a PCH decl is modified.
5864  if (RD->isFromASTFile()) {
5865  // A forward reference was mutated into a definition. Rewrite it.
5866  // FIXME: This happens during template instantiation, should we
5867  // have created a new definition decl instead ?
5868  assert(isTemplateInstantiation(RD->getTemplateSpecializationKind()) &&
5869  "completed a tag from another module but not by instantiation?");
5870  DeclUpdates[RD].push_back(
5871  DeclUpdate(UPD_CXX_INSTANTIATED_CLASS_DEFINITION));
5872  }
5873  }
5874 }
5875 
5876 static bool isImportedDeclContext(ASTReader *Chain, const Decl *D) {
5877  if (D->isFromASTFile())
5878  return true;
5879 
5880  // The predefined __va_list_tag struct is imported if we imported any decls.
5881  // FIXME: This is a gross hack.
5882  return D == D->getASTContext().getVaListTagDecl();
5883 }
5884 
5885 void ASTWriter::AddedVisibleDecl(const DeclContext *DC, const Decl *D) {
5886  if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
5887  assert(DC->isLookupContext() &&
5888  "Should not add lookup results to non-lookup contexts!");
5889 
5890  // TU is handled elsewhere.
5891  if (isa<TranslationUnitDecl>(DC))
5892  return;
5893 
5894  // Namespaces are handled elsewhere, except for template instantiations of
5895  // FunctionTemplateDecls in namespaces. We are interested in cases where the
5896  // local instantiations are added to an imported context. Only happens when
5897  // adding ADL lookup candidates, for example templated friends.
5898  if (isa<NamespaceDecl>(DC) && D->getFriendObjectKind() == Decl::FOK_None &&
5899  !isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D))
5900  return;
5901 
5902  // We're only interested in cases where a local declaration is added to an
5903  // imported context.
5904  if (D->isFromASTFile() || !isImportedDeclContext(Chain, cast<Decl>(DC)))
5905  return;
5906 
5907  assert(DC == DC->getPrimaryContext() && "added to non-primary context");
5908  assert(!getDefinitiveDeclContext(DC) && "DeclContext not definitive!");
5909  assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
5910  if (UpdatedDeclContexts.insert(DC) && !cast<Decl>(DC)->isFromASTFile()) {
5911  // We're adding a visible declaration to a predefined decl context. Ensure
5912  // that we write out all of its lookup results so we don't get a nasty
5913  // surprise when we try to emit its lookup table.
5914  llvm::append_range(DeclsToEmitEvenIfUnreferenced, DC->decls());
5915  }
5916  DeclsToEmitEvenIfUnreferenced.push_back(D);
5917 }
5918 
5919 void ASTWriter::AddedCXXImplicitMember(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const Decl *D) {
5920  if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
5921  assert(D->isImplicit());
5922 
5923  // We're only interested in cases where a local declaration is added to an
5924  // imported context.
5925  if (D->isFromASTFile() || !isImportedDeclContext(Chain, RD))
5926  return;
5927 
5928  if (!isa<CXXMethodDecl>(D))
5929  return;
5930 
5931  // A decl coming from PCH was modified.
5932  assert(RD->isCompleteDefinition());
5933  assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
5934  DeclUpdates[RD].push_back(DeclUpdate(UPD_CXX_ADDED_IMPLICIT_MEMBER, D));
5935 }

5937 void ASTWriter::ResolvedExceptionSpec(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
5938  if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
5939  assert(!DoneWritingDeclsAndTypes && "Already done writing updates!");
5940  if (!Chain) return;
5941  Chain->forEachImportedKeyDecl(FD, [&](const Decl *D) {
5942  // If we don't already know the exception specification for this redecl
5943  // chain, add an update record for it.
5944  if (isUnresolvedExceptionSpec(cast<FunctionDecl>(D)
5945  ->getType()
5946  ->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()
5947  ->getExceptionSpecType()))
5948  DeclUpdates[D].push_back(UPD_CXX_RESOLVED_EXCEPTION_SPEC);
5949  });
5950 }

6002 void ASTWriter::InstantiationRequested(const ValueDecl *D) {

6006  return;

6049 void ASTWriter::DeclarationMarkedUsed(const Decl *D) {
6050  if (Chain && Chain->isProcessingUpdateRecords()) return;
6051  assert(!WritingAST && "Already writing the AST!");
6052

6054  // we can skip writing the update record. We make sure that isUsed() triggers
6055  // completion of the redeclaration chain of the entity.
6056  for (auto Prev = D->getMostRecentDecl(); Prev; Prev = Prev->getPreviousDecl())
6057  if (IsLocalDecl(Prev))
6058  return;
6059

6154  OMPClauseWriter(ASTRecordWriter &Record) : Record(Record) {}
6155 #define GEN_CLANG_CLAUSE_CLASS
6156 #define CLAUSE_CLASS(Enum, Str, Class) void Visit##Class(Class *S);

6169 void OMPClauseWriter::writeClause(OMPClause *C) {
6170  Record.push_back(unsigned(C->getClauseKind()));
6171  Visit(C);
6172  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getBeginLoc());
6173  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getEndLoc());
6174 }

6177  Record.push_back(uint64_t(C->getCaptureRegion()));
6178  Record.AddStmt(C->getPreInitStmt());

6675 void OMPClauseWriter::VisitOMPToClause(OMPToClause *C) {

6679  Record.push_back(C->getTotalComponentsNum());
6680  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getLParenLoc());
6681  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumberOfOMPMotionModifiers; ++I) {
6682  Record.push_back(C->getMotionModifier(I));
6683  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getMotionModifierLoc(I));
6684  }
6685  Record.AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(C->getMapperQualifierLoc());
6686  Record.AddDeclarationNameInfo(C->getMapperIdInfo());

6688  for (auto *E : C->varlists())

6690  for (auto *E : C->mapperlists())
6691  Record.AddStmt(E);
6692  for (auto *D : C->all_decls())
6693  Record.AddDeclRef(D);
6694  for (auto N : C->all_num_lists())
6695  Record.push_back(N);
6696  for (auto N : C->all_lists_sizes())
6697  Record.push_back(N);
6698  for (auto &M : C->all_components()) {
6699  Record.AddStmt(M.getAssociatedExpression());
6700  Record.writeBool(M.isNonContiguous());
6701  Record.AddDeclRef(M.getAssociatedDeclaration());
6702  }

6705 void OMPClauseWriter::VisitOMPFromClause(OMPFromClause *C) {
6706  Record.push_back(C->varlist_size());
6707  Record.push_back(C->getUniqueDeclarationsNum());
6708  Record.push_back(C->getTotalComponentListNum());
6709  Record.push_back(C->getTotalComponentsNum());
6710  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getLParenLoc());
6711  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumberOfOMPMotionModifiers; ++I) {
6712  Record.push_back(C->getMotionModifier(I));
6713  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getMotionModifierLoc(I));
6714  }
6715  Record.AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(C->getMapperQualifierLoc());
6716  Record.AddDeclarationNameInfo(C->getMapperIdInfo());
6717  Record.AddSourceLocation(C->getColonLoc());
6718  for (auto *E : C->varlists())
6719  Record.AddStmt(E);
6720  for (auto *E : C->mapperlists())
6721  Record.AddStmt(E);
6722  for (auto *D : C->all_decls())
6723  Record.AddDeclRef(D);
6724  for (auto N : C->all_num_lists())
6725  Record.push_back(N);
6726  for (auto N : C->all_lists_sizes())
6727  Record.push_back(N);
6728  for (auto &M : C->all_components()) {
6729  Record.AddStmt(M.getAssociatedExpression());
6730  Record.writeBool(M.isNonContiguous());
6731  Record.AddDeclRef(M.getAssociatedDeclaration());
6732  }
6733 }

6873 void ASTRecordWriter::writeOMPTraitInfo(const OMPTraitInfo *TI) {
6874  writeUInt32(TI->Sets.size());
6875  for (const auto &Set : TI->Sets) {
6876  writeEnum(Set.Kind);
6877  writeUInt32(Set.Selectors.size());
6878  for (const auto &Selector : Set.Selectors) {
6879  writeEnum(Selector.Kind);
6880  writeBool(Selector.ScoreOrCondition);
6881  if (Selector.ScoreOrCondition)
6882  writeExprRef(Selector.ScoreOrCondition);
6883  writeUInt32(Selector.Properties.size());
6884  for (const auto &Property : Selector.Properties)
6885  writeEnum(Property.Kind);
6886  }
6887  }
6888 }
6889 
6890 void ASTRecordWriter::writeOMPChildren(OMPChildren *Data) {
6891  if (!Data)
6892  return;
6893  writeUInt32(Data->getNumClauses());
6894  writeUInt32(Data->getNumChildren());
6895  writeBool(Data->hasAssociatedStmt());
6896  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Data->getNumClauses(); I < E; ++I)
6897  writeOMPClause(Data->getClauses()[I]);
6898  if (Data->hasAssociatedStmt())
6899  AddStmt(Data->getAssociatedStmt());
6900  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Data->getNumChildren(); I < E; ++I)
6901  AddStmt(Data->getChildren()[I]);
6902 }
